In no particular order.

* Add specs to project for TDD.

* Implement optional smtp_settings directive to pass to the mail gem. So people can do the following:

smtp_settings = { 	:address              => "smtp.gmail.com",
            		:port                 => 587,
            		:domain               => 'your.host.name',
		            :user_name            => '<username>',
		            :password             => '<password>',
		            :authentication       => 'plain',
		            :enable_starttls_auto => true  }
            
rcj = RubyCronJob.new do |script|
	script.author     		= 'John Doe'
 	script.name       		= 'test'
 	script.mailto     		= 'john@doe.com'
 	script.mailfrom   		= 'root@doe.com'
	script.smtp_settings 	= smtp_settings
end

* Implement optional :template directive for using a custom ERB template:

script.template 	= "./myTemplate"